Caleb Van "Tex" Warrington Jr. (March 21, 1921 – September 21, 1983) was a professional American football player for the All-America Football Conference (AAFC)'s Brooklyn Dodgers. He played in 39 games between 1946 and 1948 after his collegiate career at William & Mary (1942) and Auburn (1944). In 1978, he was inducted into the Delaware Sports Hall of Fame.
